---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Jorge R. Obando | Author of The Tracks Remember"
  description="Learn more about Jorge R. Obando and the story behind The Tracks Remember and Trains and Castles."
>
  <Hero
    title="About Jorge"
    subtitle="Writing as a way of remembering, observing, and making meaning."
  />

  <Section>
    <p>
      Jorge R. Obando is a writer, builder, and observer of the moments that often pass unnoticed.
    </p>
    <p>
      His work explores memory, place, movement, family, and the emotional weight carried by
      ordinary experiences. Rather than separating reflection from everyday life, he writes from
      the belief that meaning often lives inside the small details—the landscapes we move through,
      the conversations we remember, the routes that shape us without asking permission.
    </p>
    <p>
      The Tracks Remember and Trains and Castles emerged from one shared journey, told through
      two different lenses. One is reflective and literary. The other is child-centered, immediate,
      and full of wonder.
    </p>
    <p>
      Ari’s presence is part of that journey too—not only in life, but in the emotional foundation
      that helped these books take shape.
    </p>
    <p>
      Together, the books form the beginning of a wider creative and digital project: one that connects
      story, memory, place, and experience across physical and online spaces.
    </p>
    <a
  class="button"
  href="https://jorgerobando.com"
  target="_blank"
  rel="noopener noreferrer"
>
  Visit Jorge's Author Hub
</a>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>